OL,3,CMale 'Hoff' crab has bigger claws to
OL,4,Cfight other males for a mate
OL,6,FThe species, which has the official
OL,7,Fname of Kiwa tyleri, lives in large
OL,8,Fcommunities around hot vents on the
OL,9,Fseafloor in Antarctica, and its many
OL,10,Fhairs host bacteria which the crab
OL,11,Ffeeds on.
OL,13,FThe latest study examined 135 of the
OL,14,Fcrabs - which are part of the Kiwaidae
OL,15,Ffamily which are also known as "yeti
OL,16,Fcrabs" because of their bristly
OL,17,Fappearance, at the East Scotia Ridge
OL,18,Fin the Scotia Sea.
