OL,3,CMale 'Hoff' crab has bigger claws to
OL,4,Cfight other males for a mate
OL,6,F"Knowing that there's a difference in
OL,7,Fsize between the male and female claws
OL,8,Fhelps us understand the behaviour and
OL,9,Fecology of the yeti crab family -
OL,10,Fwhich we know little about because
OL,11,Fthey are a fairly recent discovery,
OL,12,Fand their home is very difficult to
OL,13,Freach.
OL,15,F"Physical differences between males
OL,16,Fand females is a common feature of
OL,17,Fdecapod crustaceans which live in
OL,18,Fshallow water, and usually it's
OL,19,Fbecause the male is forced to guard
OL,20,Fthe mate, or females have to divert
OL,21,Ftheir growth energy for reproduction."
OL,26,@nD@AOUwD@AOU}D@fO]
